WEBVTT

01:25.900 --> 01:34.930
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

01:35.440 --> 01:37.860
[Episode 24]

01:38.430 --> 01:39.229
Mr. Director,

01:40.289 --> 01:43.060
Actually, I have

01:43.120 --> 01:45.570
quite a few companies of similar size

01:46.090 --> 01:47.900
in mainland China.

01:49.420 --> 01:51.200
Your asking price today

01:51.310 --> 01:52.370
isn't exactly low.

01:55.500 --> 01:56.100
Mr. Huang,

01:57.120 --> 01:58.070
like I said

01:58.070 --> 01:58.890
earlier,

01:59.229 --> 01:59.950
we're not really looking to

01:59.950 --> 02:01.240
sell this factory.

02:01.620 --> 02:03.650
This is already the absolute lowest price

02:03.650 --> 02:04.660
we can accept.

02:05.480 --> 02:07.930
If you think it's not a good deal,

02:08.190 --> 02:09.970
then we have no choice...

02:11.740 --> 02:12.860
If you're not selling,

02:12.860 --> 02:15.180
then why even call me here?

02:15.690 --> 02:17.290
I... I want to say something.

02:18.000 --> 02:18.600
Mr. Huang,

02:18.740 --> 02:19.340
I think the

02:19.340 --> 02:20.560
sale of the factory

02:20.870 --> 02:21.870
is a sure thing,

02:21.960 --> 02:23.250
right?

02:25.310 --> 02:26.840
He probably just wants

02:27.460 --> 02:28.800
to sell it to the highest bidder.

02:28.800 --> 02:31.130
I think besides the

02:31.240 --> 02:32.640
three bosses here today,

02:32.680 --> 02:33.900
there really are

02:34.210 --> 02:35.520
many other bosses outside

02:35.520 --> 02:36.240
who are keeping an eye on

02:36.240 --> 02:37.740
the movements of this factory.

02:37.740 --> 02:38.140
Right?

02:39.680 --> 02:41.000
Yes.

02:43.030 --> 02:43.829
I understand.

02:45.180 --> 02:47.579
I will go back
and think about it carefully.

02:48.400 --> 02:49.130
I...

02:49.970 --> 02:50.430
Come in!

02:50.670 --> 02:53.730
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

02:50.690 --> 02:51.190
Director,

02:51.190 --> 02:52.280
there is an overseas call.

02:52.280 --> 02:53.860
He says he also wants to buy our factory.

02:53.860 --> 02:54.590
An overseas call?

02:54.590 --> 02:54.970
Yes.

02:56.840 --> 02:58.280
I'm going to take the call.

02:58.280 --> 03:00.000
Mr. Huang, wait for me a moment.

03:00.000 --> 03:01.060
I'll be right back.

03:01.590 --> 03:02.450
I'll be right back.

03:02.450 --> 03:05.880
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

03:02.620 --> 03:03.800
Wait for me.

03:06.870 --> 03:08.430
Then I will go to the restroom.

03:08.430 --> 03:09.360
I'll go with you.

03:09.880 --> 03:17.410
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

03:09.970 --> 03:10.560
No need.

03:10.630 --> 03:11.630
I know where it is.

03:14.090 --> 03:14.860
On the left.

03:15.000 --> 03:16.130
Do you need company?

03:22.210 --> 03:23.060
If I'm not mistaken,

03:23.060 --> 03:23.579
you are

03:23.590 --> 03:25.720
shills hired by Director Wang, right?

03:28.410 --> 03:29.620
I can tell at a glance.

03:30.470 --> 03:31.340
What are you doing?

03:31.340 --> 03:32.900
Is this how you act as shills?

03:32.900 --> 03:34.090
Are you putting on a play?

03:34.090 --> 03:35.620
We are doing big business.

03:35.640 --> 03:36.840
Can you act like this?

03:37.210 --> 03:38.940
Was the phone call also a setup?

03:39.810 --> 03:41.270
"I have an overseas call."

03:41.690 --> 03:43.630
What are you talking about?

03:43.650 --> 03:44.250
You can't run a business like this,
can you?

03:44.250 --> 03:44.620
If you do that,

03:44.620 --> 03:46.030
you'll ruin the business.

03:46.030 --> 03:47.430
You two should leave now.

03:48.050 --> 03:50.020
[Negotiation Meeting on
Foreign Investment Partnership]

03:48.210 --> 03:50.079
Come on, you don't even know
how shills behave.

03:50.079 --> 03:52.880
I made it to the finals
of the singing competition.

03:53.870 --> 03:54.800
Did you listen to

03:54.820 --> 03:55.530
the new song I sent you?

03:55.530 --> 03:56.060
How is it?

03:56.579 --> 03:58.680
Of course, it's incredibly good.

04:00.910 --> 04:01.770
By the way, Mom,

04:01.780 --> 04:02.970
I called you a couple of times
these past few days,

04:02.970 --> 04:04.230
why didn't you pick up?

04:04.500 --> 04:06.160
Were you and Mr. Ye not at home?

04:07.400 --> 04:08.550
We've been out

04:08.710 --> 04:10.250
traveling these past couple of days.

04:10.250 --> 04:12.250
We are at Mrs. Xu's house now.

04:12.410 --> 04:13.580
I didn't want you to worry,

04:13.580 --> 04:15.640
so I called you back as soon as I could.

04:15.870 --> 04:17.790
When is your final?

04:18.220 --> 04:19.279
It's in two months.

04:20.430 --> 04:22.380
Then prepare well.

04:22.870 --> 04:23.800
I will be waiting

04:23.920 --> 04:25.690
in front of the TV

04:25.750 --> 04:26.480
to watch you.

04:27.060 --> 04:27.930
Definitely.

04:29.130 --> 04:29.730
All right.

04:29.860 --> 04:30.930
Then you catch up with Mrs. Xu.

04:30.930 --> 04:32.060
I won't disturb you.

04:32.610 --> 04:33.500
Go get busy.

04:34.510 --> 04:35.420
I miss you.

04:35.630 --> 04:36.159
Bye-bye.

04:44.300 --> 04:45.010
Mr. Huang,

04:45.010 --> 04:46.920
you offered the lowest price,

04:47.310 --> 04:48.600
but seeing your sincerity,

04:48.600 --> 04:50.330
we agree to cooperate with you.

04:51.270 --> 04:52.510
But if you want to lay off staff,

04:52.510 --> 04:54.110
I really can't agree to that.

04:54.500 --> 04:55.310
Mr. Wang,

04:55.390 --> 04:57.520
I completely understand how you feel.

04:57.750 --> 04:58.920
But there are really

04:58.920 --> 05:00.570
too many workers in the factory.

05:00.570 --> 05:01.850
Such a huge expense,

05:01.900 --> 05:03.530
who can afford it?

05:04.050 --> 05:05.540
That may be true,

05:05.660 --> 05:07.720
but how do I explain this to everyone?

05:08.510 --> 05:09.750
Some veteran workers have been
in the factory

05:09.750 --> 05:11.080
for most of their lives.

05:14.420 --> 05:14.870
Come on.

05:14.690 --> 05:22.420
[Jingyi Weida Motor Parts Factory]

05:15.160 --> 05:16.160
I have a proposal.

05:16.180 --> 05:17.040
Come on, sit down.

05:17.040 --> 05:17.770
Take it easy.

05:17.950 --> 05:18.890
Take it easy. Sit down.

05:18.890 --> 05:19.510
Sit down.

05:19.600 --> 05:20.260
Look, look.

05:20.310 --> 05:21.420
He wants to buy, and you want to sell.

05:21.420 --> 05:23.220
We should make it happen, right?

05:23.660 --> 05:24.320
Do the math.

05:24.660 --> 05:25.560
If you really

05:25.560 --> 05:27.160
lay off all those employees,

05:27.510 --> 05:29.250
why don't we give each family

05:29.310 --> 05:30.800
some relocation allowances?

05:30.800 --> 05:31.330
This way,

05:31.430 --> 05:32.810
Mr. Huang might feel a bit better,

05:32.810 --> 05:33.240
right?

05:34.190 --> 05:36.460
It's not about the money.

05:34.740 --> 05:37.140
[Jingyi Weida Motor Parts Factory]

05:37.100 --> 05:38.720
Do you know how deeply attached

05:38.720 --> 05:39.659
those veteran workers

05:39.659 --> 05:41.110
are to our factory?

05:41.500 --> 05:42.810
They already treat this factory

05:42.810 --> 05:44.500
as their own home.

05:44.570 --> 05:45.770
I have a proposal too.

05:46.480 --> 05:48.340
I understand what you're saying.

05:48.680 --> 05:50.860
This is the livelihood
of three generations.

05:50.860 --> 05:53.060
How can you just take away
their jobs like that?

05:53.060 --> 05:54.870
You can't just lay them off.

05:55.070 --> 05:57.370
You...

05:57.570 --> 05:59.190
His proposal doesn't count.

05:59.300 --> 06:00.220
What are you doing?

06:00.220 --> 06:02.250
The three of us are just discussing it.

06:02.250 --> 06:03.420
Why are you butting in?

06:03.420 --> 06:05.080
What did you even understand?

06:05.120 --> 06:05.840
Um, how about this.

06:05.840 --> 06:07.810
It's very easy for us to calculate.

06:07.860 --> 06:09.330
We get business

06:09.330 --> 06:10.190
for this guy named Huang,

06:10.190 --> 06:11.650
not only is he ungrateful,

06:11.830 --> 06:14.130
but he also acts like
we can't do without him.

06:14.130 --> 06:15.870
He simply looks down on us.

06:15.890 --> 06:17.740
Doing business with him
is too frustrating.

06:17.740 --> 06:18.540
I'm not doing.

06:18.770 --> 06:20.330
I'm not doing this business anymore.

06:20.330 --> 06:21.890
Whether he looks down on us or not

06:21.890 --> 06:23.470
isn't important, right?

06:23.770 --> 06:24.480
What matters is

06:24.480 --> 06:26.270
that money

06:26.300 --> 06:27.630
doesn't look down on us.

06:30.330 --> 06:32.180
Not only is he forcing the price down,

06:32.180 --> 06:34.240
but he's even driving the workers out.

06:34.240 --> 06:36.270
Isn't that taking away their livelihood?

06:36.270 --> 06:38.130
How are they supposed to survive?

06:38.250 --> 06:39.010
What's that got to do

06:39.010 --> 06:40.370
with you?

06:41.560 --> 06:41.950
Liangliang,

06:41.950 --> 06:42.920
I know you are

06:43.370 --> 06:44.390
soft-hearted.

06:45.100 --> 06:45.500
No.

06:45.500 --> 06:46.370
But look,

06:46.950 --> 06:48.070
does any soft-hearted person

06:48.070 --> 06:49.250
ever end up well?

06:50.420 --> 06:51.930
Our goal is to make money.

06:52.310 --> 06:53.170
Look at that...

06:53.810 --> 06:55.770
The grandpa in Calabash Brothers.

06:55.860 --> 06:56.510
He was soft-hearted,

06:56.510 --> 06:57.070
and didn't he

06:57.070 --> 06:58.330
end up being captured by the Snake Spirit?

06:58.330 --> 06:59.360
But we can't harm people

06:59.360 --> 07:00.160
just to make money, right?

07:00.160 --> 07:01.420
Who's harming people?

07:01.420 --> 07:02.870
Did you? Did I?

07:02.930 --> 07:03.870
He did!

07:03.870 --> 07:05.130
How did he harm people?

07:05.130 --> 07:06.590
Right? Harming people...

07:07.310 --> 07:08.450
The Snake Spirit harmed the grandpa.

07:08.450 --> 07:10.130
What does that have to do with us?

07:10.130 --> 07:11.190
We are businessmen.

07:11.190 --> 07:13.190
We're just making the middleman's cut,

07:13.190 --> 07:14.950
by introducing them to each other.

07:14.950 --> 07:16.560
What does it have to do with us?

07:16.560 --> 07:17.040
Besides,

07:17.040 --> 07:19.370
didn't they give relocation allowances?

07:21.060 --> 07:23.180
Just look at how this Huang guy

07:23.180 --> 07:24.440
pushed the price down.

07:25.540 --> 07:26.600
Yeah, he says he'll pay
relocation allowances—

07:26.600 --> 07:27.570
but will he actually?

07:27.570 --> 07:29.100
And even if he does,
how much is it gonna be?

07:29.100 --> 07:29.750
What's that

07:29.750 --> 07:31.100
got to do with us?

07:31.930 --> 07:33.070
Liangliang, I'm telling you the truth.

07:33.070 --> 07:34.400
If we close this deal,

07:34.680 --> 07:36.340
we'll make big money, right?

07:36.450 --> 07:37.680
And if you feel like giving
relocation allowances,

07:37.680 --> 07:38.480
then go ahead.

07:39.070 --> 07:40.200
But with this money,

07:40.310 --> 07:40.770
you...

07:40.830 --> 07:42.220
Don't you like playing the saxophone?

07:42.220 --> 07:43.180
You can play it

07:43.190 --> 07:44.120
wherever you want.

07:44.120 --> 07:44.600
You can even go to

07:44.600 --> 07:46.070
the Golden Hall in Vienna.

07:46.620 --> 07:47.390
If it breaks

07:47.390 --> 07:48.790
so many people's hearts,

07:49.070 --> 07:51.470
I don't have to go to the Golden Hall.

07:51.570 --> 07:52.830
Like you'd even get the chance to go

07:52.830 --> 07:53.760
if you wanted to.

07:54.750 --> 07:56.390
Seriously, I can't talk to you.

07:56.390 --> 07:57.030
Hurry up.

07:57.450 --> 07:59.380
Go get caught by that Snake Spirit.

08:01.860 --> 08:02.460
It's fine.

08:02.810 --> 08:03.670
Let me feed you.

08:06.560 --> 08:07.290
Here, drink.

08:09.660 --> 08:10.260
It's okay.

08:10.600 --> 08:11.130
Drink up.

08:19.120 --> 08:21.520
[Tuesday, August 15, 1995]

08:40.700 --> 08:42.000
Sleep.

08:42.240 --> 08:44.650
You'll hear the sound tomorrow.

08:51.250 --> 08:52.600
Listen, Ranran.

08:52.630 --> 08:53.690
You should go back.

08:54.580 --> 08:55.440
I'll wait for you to come back.

08:55.440 --> 08:56.120
Okay.

08:59.660 --> 09:01.450
[Director's Office]

09:01.940 --> 09:02.990
Mr. Wang.

09:02.470 --> 09:03.670
[Director's Office]

09:03.810 --> 09:04.410
Mr. Huang.

09:04.500 --> 09:05.530
Hope I'm not bothering you.

09:05.530 --> 09:06.580
Not at all.

09:10.770 --> 09:11.460
This is a photo

09:11.460 --> 09:12.940
we took together

09:12.940 --> 09:14.290
when we worked a project a while ago.

09:14.290 --> 09:15.080
Not long ago.

09:15.410 --> 09:17.290
I just met Ma too.

09:18.130 --> 09:18.780
Is that so?

09:19.460 --> 09:20.740
I just met Mr. Ma

09:21.080 --> 09:22.410
recently myself.

09:30.430 --> 09:32.660
Mr. Huang, why are you coming to see me?

09:33.480 --> 09:33.870
Yes.

09:34.040 --> 09:37.240
[Hong Kong butterfly pastry]

09:34.580 --> 09:35.680
I brought these from Hong Kong

09:35.680 --> 09:37.070
especially for you.

09:38.470 --> 09:39.600
I can't accept this.

09:39.890 --> 09:41.220
It's against the rules.

09:42.050 --> 09:42.850
Look closely.

09:44.980 --> 09:46.240
The butterfly pastry.

09:46.310 --> 09:47.710
It's not even worth much.

09:48.460 --> 09:50.790
It's just about building relationships.

09:53.140 --> 09:54.340
Why don't you try one?

09:54.500 --> 09:55.580
They're delicious.

09:55.580 --> 09:56.180
All right,

09:56.610 --> 09:57.870
I won't be polite then.

09:59.010 --> 10:00.940
[Hong Kong Butterfly Pastry]

10:03.190 --> 10:04.340
How is it? Good?

10:05.890 --> 10:06.890
Crispy and sweet.

10:08.530 --> 10:10.290
Actually, we can negotiate

10:10.410 --> 10:12.480
the price slowly.

10:13.010 --> 10:14.940
The most important thing
is our relationship.

10:14.940 --> 10:16.290
With a good relationship,

10:16.290 --> 10:17.820
everything is negotiable.

10:19.450 --> 10:22.560
Please look after us, Mr. Huang.

10:23.740 --> 10:24.340
By the way,

10:24.740 --> 10:26.200
these butterfly pastries

10:26.860 --> 10:28.020
should be eaten soon.

10:28.020 --> 10:29.280
They don't keep long.

10:33.340 --> 10:33.870
Okay.

10:33.890 --> 10:35.150
Then I won't hold back.

10:35.840 --> 10:36.170
Okay.

10:36.480 --> 10:38.320
I'll be heading back now.

10:38.500 --> 10:39.100
All right.

10:39.220 --> 10:39.910
You go ahead,

10:39.910 --> 10:40.670
I'll be right there.

10:40.670 --> 10:41.510
Okay.

11:00.200 --> 11:00.630
Mom!

11:02.500 --> 11:02.870
Dad.

11:03.100 --> 11:05.010
Mom can hear me call her Mom.

11:05.270 --> 11:06.540
Silly boy.

11:08.910 --> 11:10.520
You silly boy.

11:10.720 --> 11:12.180
Wipe your sweat. Hurry up.

11:13.080 --> 11:15.510
Your mom can hear things.

11:15.530 --> 11:17.170
But she can't make out what you're saying.

11:17.170 --> 11:17.860
Got it?

11:18.130 --> 11:20.100
Otherwise what would the cochlear implant
even be for?

11:20.100 --> 11:21.130
If it worked all at once,

11:21.130 --> 11:22.770
wouldn't your mom be like a TV—

11:22.770 --> 11:25.500
hearing everything
the moment it's switched on?

11:26.550 --> 11:27.880
If you don't believe me,

11:28.790 --> 11:31.460
try calling her Dad.

11:32.360 --> 11:33.050
Dad.

11:35.220 --> 11:36.530
There's a reaction, but...

11:36.530 --> 11:39.090
What did you hear?

11:42.500 --> 11:43.950
See? She heard a "buzz"

11:43.970 --> 11:44.910
right?

11:45.650 --> 11:47.660
When will Mom be able to hear

11:47.690 --> 11:48.970
me call her Mom?

11:48.990 --> 11:50.590
Xiaobao, don't rush it.

11:50.650 --> 11:51.510
The doctor said

11:51.530 --> 11:52.340
it'll take 3 to 6 months

11:52.340 --> 11:53.670
for her to recover normal hearing,

11:53.670 --> 11:55.750
and then she can slowly start speaking.

11:55.750 --> 11:56.540
Auntie,

11:57.520 --> 12:00.420
don't rush.

12:00.670 --> 12:02.290
Take your time.

12:03.840 --> 12:07.890
I'm not rushing.

12:08.770 --> 12:10.050
Take it easy.

12:12.440 --> 12:14.400
Then I'll call my Mom
every day from now on.

12:14.400 --> 12:15.730
That won't work either.

12:16.010 --> 12:18.610
You have to talk to your mother
about everything.

12:18.610 --> 12:20.080
Gesture less.

12:20.460 --> 12:20.910
You know?

12:20.910 --> 12:23.440
Let your mother get used to your speech,

12:24.050 --> 12:24.630
you know?

12:25.780 --> 12:27.290
Don't keep calling for your mother.

12:27.290 --> 12:29.080
Otherwise the people
in the courtyard will talk,

12:29.080 --> 12:30.810
wondering why there's

12:30.840 --> 12:32.390
a tadpole in our courtyard,

12:32.890 --> 12:34.330
looking for its mom.

12:46.200 --> 12:47.200
Mr. Chen,

12:48.950 --> 12:50.830
give me some time.

12:51.480 --> 12:52.510
Mr. Wang.

12:53.150 --> 12:54.510
My dear Director Wang,

12:55.600 --> 12:56.720
It's extremely urgent.

12:56.720 --> 12:58.650
How long are you going to put it off?

12:59.080 --> 12:59.890
Please

13:00.700 --> 13:02.160
give me a little more time.

13:02.840 --> 13:05.570
If I give you time,
who will give the factory time?

13:54.530 --> 13:55.000
Hello?

13:57.340 --> 13:58.700
It's been days.

13:58.700 --> 14:00.760
Why is there no news from either side?

14:01.000 --> 14:02.030
Mr. Huang has stopped rushing us,

14:02.030 --> 14:04.560
and Director Wang
isn't answering his phone.

14:05.170 --> 14:06.450
I think Director Wang

14:07.170 --> 14:08.480
doesn't want to see us.

14:12.160 --> 14:14.160
Does he not want to sell the factory?

14:14.820 --> 14:15.720
If he doesn't want to sell it,

14:15.720 --> 14:16.960
there's no need to hide from us.

14:16.960 --> 14:19.120
Then he must have found a buyer himself

14:19.120 --> 14:20.920
and is too embarrassed to see us.

14:22.700 --> 14:24.210
That won't do.

14:24.240 --> 14:25.550
Mr. Huang is waiting for

14:25.550 --> 14:26.550
an answer from us.

14:26.550 --> 14:28.350
We can't just leave him hanging.

14:28.550 --> 14:29.270
I see.

14:31.320 --> 14:32.120
Director Wang

14:33.510 --> 14:34.940
is not a good person.

14:36.080 --> 14:38.410
He's not the Calabash Brothers' grandpa,

14:38.720 --> 14:40.050
but the Scorpion Demon.

14:41.290 --> 14:44.930
[Jingyi Weida
Electrical Equipment Service Center]

14:48.630 --> 14:49.830
Mr. Huang, Mr. Huang.

14:50.960 --> 14:51.870
Director Wang.

14:51.890 --> 14:53.200
Thanks for your hard work.

14:53.200 --> 14:54.000
We meet again.

14:54.530 --> 14:55.120
Thank you.

14:55.120 --> 14:55.720
Sorry.

14:55.720 --> 14:57.120
You know I'm a neat freak.

14:58.220 --> 14:59.620
I understand.

15:00.370 --> 15:01.770
Let's talk inside.

15:01.870 --> 15:02.460
Alright, after you.

15:02.460 --> 15:02.990
Let's go.

15:17.240 --> 15:17.940
How did the two of them

15:17.940 --> 15:18.870
get together?

15:21.210 --> 15:23.220
The Snake Spirit and the Scorpion Demon
have joined forces.

15:23.220 --> 15:24.750
I said no entry, so you can't go in.

15:24.750 --> 15:26.080
Why are you so stubborn?

15:26.120 --> 15:26.600
Can't you just

15:26.600 --> 15:27.510
call your Director?

15:27.510 --> 15:28.000
Wouldn't that solve it?

15:28.000 --> 15:29.170
My cell phone has no signal.

15:29.170 --> 15:30.250
How do I know who you are?

15:30.250 --> 15:31.270
I'm Mr. Ma.

15:31.480 --> 15:32.750
Tell him it's Manager Ma,

15:32.750 --> 15:33.550
Lucky Ma.

15:34.510 --> 15:35.840
So you are Manager Lucky Ma.

15:35.840 --> 15:37.410
Yes, I'm the one
helping you sell the factory.

15:37.410 --> 15:39.000
You're going to sell our entire factory?

15:39.000 --> 15:39.530
Yes.

15:39.820 --> 15:41.150
Okay, I understand.

15:41.360 --> 15:42.130
Is it just the two of you?

15:42.130 --> 15:42.530
Yes.

15:42.770 --> 15:43.480
All right.

15:44.100 --> 15:45.450
Please come in, Mr. Ma.

15:45.600 --> 15:46.660
I'll go make a call.

15:46.870 --> 15:47.960
I could have called myself,

15:47.960 --> 15:48.600
my phone just

15:48.600 --> 15:49.860
has no signal in your broken factory.

15:49.860 --> 15:50.720
Okay.

15:58.580 --> 15:59.180
Stubborn.

15:59.910 --> 16:00.510
At his age,

16:00.510 --> 16:02.240
no wonder he's still a security guard.

16:02.240 --> 16:03.170
If I were his age,

16:03.200 --> 16:04.170
I'd be the Director.

16:04.170 --> 16:05.630
You're definitely more promising than him.

16:05.630 --> 16:06.040
Yeah.

16:06.110 --> 16:06.700
Let me tell you,

16:06.700 --> 16:07.360
if you ever do this job in the future,

16:07.360 --> 16:07.910
and I find out,

16:07.910 --> 16:08.860
I'll look down on you.

16:08.860 --> 16:09.360
When I'm old,

16:09.360 --> 16:11.000
I'll still be playing the saxophone.

16:11.000 --> 16:12.250
Where can you play the saxophone
when you're old?

16:12.250 --> 16:13.500
I'll play in the park.

16:13.550 --> 16:14.250
While the old ladies are dancing,

16:14.250 --> 16:14.910
you'll be over there playing?

16:14.910 --> 16:16.200
It doesn't matter who I play for,

16:16.200 --> 16:18.720
I'll definitely play the saxophone
for the rest of my life.

16:18.720 --> 16:19.240
Keep playing.

16:19.240 --> 16:21.100
You won't even have teeth by then.

16:24.740 --> 16:26.100
He's the one surnamed Ma.

16:26.100 --> 16:26.550
Yes.

16:26.570 --> 16:28.220
He's the one who will see our factory.

16:28.220 --> 16:28.770
It's he

16:28.770 --> 16:29.550
who'll take away our livelihoods.

16:29.550 --> 16:30.200
Something's wrong.

16:30.200 --> 16:31.060
Workers,

16:31.290 --> 16:33.150
he's the one selling our factory.

16:33.340 --> 16:33.870
Beat him!

16:33.910 --> 16:34.270
Run!

16:34.790 --> 16:35.170
Run.

16:43.600 --> 16:44.400
Hurry, hurry.

16:45.240 --> 16:46.700
-Stop! Don't move!
-Stop!

16:47.510 --> 16:48.110
Don't run.

16:49.770 --> 16:50.720
Keys, keys.

16:50.740 --> 16:51.520
Car keys.

16:54.510 --> 16:55.250
Drive it.

16:56.120 --> 16:56.650
Hurry up.

16:57.910 --> 16:58.910
Stop right there.

17:00.750 --> 17:01.940
Catch it.

17:03.410 --> 17:04.310
Can't you throw it slower

17:04.310 --> 17:05.240
and lower?

17:40.950 --> 17:42.140
Dear listeners,

17:42.260 --> 17:43.200
here's a breaking update

17:43.200 --> 17:44.600
from the cultural scene.

17:44.640 --> 17:45.480
The highly anticipated

17:45.480 --> 17:46.550
realist drama

17:46.610 --> 17:47.470
[The Late Love]

17:47.480 --> 17:49.850
has officially announced
its production start date today.

17:49.850 --> 17:51.220
The film is directed by

17:51.220 --> 17:53.480
acclaimed Capital Film Studio
Weng Xingguo,

17:53.480 --> 17:55.200
with a screenplay co-written

17:55.200 --> 17:56.680
by renowned screenwriter He Sheng

17:56.680 --> 17:58.080
and newcomer Xu Shengli,

17:58.110 --> 17:59.850
after nearly 6 years in development.

17:59.850 --> 18:00.750
This is also Weng Xingguo

18:00.750 --> 18:01.880
and He Sheng's

18:01.880 --> 18:03.460
fifth feature film together.

18:03.460 --> 18:04.860
Let's all look forward to

18:05.160 --> 18:05.770
the creative spark

18:05.770 --> 18:06.700
this duo will bring
to

18:06.700 --> 18:07.870
a story

18:08.270 --> 18:10.000
about youth and dreams.

18:09.730 --> 18:13.160
[The Late Love,
written by He Sheng & Xu Shengli]

18:10.850 --> 18:13.010
Screenwriter Xu Shengli—see?

18:13.310 --> 18:14.770
It's printed right there.

18:16.610 --> 18:17.140
Careful.

18:18.200 --> 18:18.900
Look at this,

18:18.900 --> 18:19.680
we'll just stick this poster

18:19.680 --> 18:20.840
right up here.

18:21.570 --> 18:22.330
How is it?

18:22.480 --> 18:23.550
Later, Xu's poster

18:23.570 --> 18:25.550
will be put up on
the big screen at the cinema.

18:25.550 --> 18:27.060
Tao Liangliang, shut up.

18:27.090 --> 18:27.480
Who puts it

18:27.480 --> 18:28.440
on the big screen?

18:28.440 --> 18:29.810
Doesn't it go at the cinema entrance?

18:29.810 --> 18:30.680
You go stick it at the entrance.

18:30.680 --> 18:31.530
I'll stick it on the screen.

18:31.530 --> 18:32.140
Shengli,

18:32.200 --> 18:34.490
your movie is about to start shooting?

18:34.770 --> 18:35.510
Not yet.

18:36.160 --> 18:37.490
I drew the poster first.

18:37.590 --> 18:38.480
You're making a poster and

18:38.480 --> 18:39.400
you didn't ask me to do it?

18:39.400 --> 18:41.400
Then draw me a couple more, will you?

18:41.610 --> 18:42.350
We just got back

18:42.350 --> 18:44.610
and already something this big happens.

18:45.530 --> 18:46.910
Xu is the first among us

18:46.980 --> 18:48.470
to make a name for himself.

18:48.610 --> 18:49.180
Later,

18:50.240 --> 18:51.220
Shengli has to treat us

18:51.220 --> 18:52.370
to a movie.

18:53.700 --> 18:55.150
A movie? That's nothing—

18:55.420 --> 18:56.120
by then,

18:56.350 --> 18:58.110
I'll just book out the whole theater

18:58.110 --> 18:59.610
and have it all to ourselves.

18:59.610 --> 19:00.620
After watching,

19:00.770 --> 19:02.200
we'll go to the Wancheng Hotel

19:02.200 --> 19:02.860
to hang out.

19:02.920 --> 19:04.650
Just hanging out isn't enough.

19:04.660 --> 19:06.160
We need to eat.

19:06.310 --> 19:07.180
Yes.

19:07.240 --> 19:09.130
Let's not wait around.

19:09.400 --> 19:11.090
Strike while the iron is hot.

19:11.220 --> 19:12.080
Let's go then.

19:12.500 --> 19:13.200
Go where?

19:13.370 --> 19:14.520
Wancheng Hotel!

19:14.640 --> 19:15.310
Seriously?

19:15.310 --> 19:15.840
Let's go.

19:16.200 --> 19:16.910
Let's go.

19:16.940 --> 19:18.120
Right now?

19:18.180 --> 19:19.070
Then we

19:19.070 --> 19:20.160
won't be polite.

19:20.160 --> 19:21.190
I need to tidy up.

19:21.330 --> 19:21.900
I won't be polite.

19:21.900 --> 19:23.260
Wancheng Hotel.

19:24.750 --> 19:25.810
Then we have to drink a little.

19:25.810 --> 19:26.870
Easy there.

19:27.030 --> 19:28.440
I've been "easy" for 30 years—

19:28.440 --> 19:30.220
any more of that
and I'll turn into a fossil.

19:30.220 --> 19:30.750
Let's go.

19:32.450 --> 19:36.670
I have to drink half a pint every day.

19:37.720 --> 19:38.920
What are we drinking?

19:38.930 --> 19:40.240
What are we drinking?

19:41.610 --> 19:44.020
[Shichahai]

19:41.750 --> 19:43.210
Let me propose a toast.

19:43.380 --> 19:44.140
Here.

19:44.180 --> 19:45.190
Our Shengli

19:45.220 --> 19:46.980
goes from Shengli to victory.

19:47.110 --> 19:47.720
Right?

19:47.750 --> 19:49.380
May we all achieve victory.

19:49.440 --> 19:50.450
Cheers.

19:50.500 --> 19:52.480
Cheers, to Shengli.

19:56.790 --> 19:58.050
Dig in.

19:59.530 --> 20:00.570
I must

20:02.440 --> 20:06.390
propose a toast
to our great screenwriter Xu.

20:06.830 --> 20:08.460
On your first day
at Seasons Change Hostel,

20:08.460 --> 20:09.690
didn't I say

20:10.000 --> 20:11.530
you would definitely succeed?

20:11.530 --> 20:12.190
From now on,

20:12.220 --> 20:13.220
my Seasons Change Hostel

20:13.220 --> 20:15.010
can no longer be the name.

20:15.180 --> 20:17.910
It will be called
Xu Shengli's Former Residence.

20:18.240 --> 20:19.050
What are you talking about?

20:19.050 --> 20:20.450
I told you before,

20:20.830 --> 20:22.000
it's not a former residence.

20:22.000 --> 20:23.660
It's an old residence.

20:23.690 --> 20:25.510
That's the place where Xu Shengli

20:25.510 --> 20:27.010
-fought.
-Yes.

20:27.700 --> 20:29.420
You are the screenwriter.
I'll listen to you.

20:29.420 --> 20:31.350
I'll be called whatever you write.

20:36.240 --> 20:36.900
Well,

20:36.900 --> 20:38.500
let's have a drink together.

20:38.810 --> 20:39.830
You two go ahead and drink first.

20:39.830 --> 20:41.050
Let's all drink together.

20:41.050 --> 20:42.330
Let's all drink together.

20:42.330 --> 20:43.240
Come on, let's have a drink together.

20:43.240 --> 20:44.270
Cheers.
Come on.

20:44.330 --> 20:45.270
Three glasses in a row.

20:45.270 --> 20:45.700
Come on.

20:45.700 --> 20:47.960
-Three glasses in a row.
-Another glass!

20:51.050 --> 20:52.050
Are you not happy?

20:52.880 --> 20:54.540
I'm happy if you all are happy.

20:55.750 --> 20:56.280
Shengli,

20:57.140 --> 20:58.940
I want to toast you alone.

21:00.640 --> 21:01.440
In the future,

21:02.420 --> 21:04.250
if you have another movie released,

21:04.250 --> 21:05.180
I'm not kidding,

21:05.720 --> 21:07.570
you should really consider
letting me draw the poster.

21:07.570 --> 21:09.330
I told you today,

21:10.220 --> 21:12.350
you can draw the poster for this movie.

21:12.550 --> 21:13.980
As long as you draw it,

21:14.000 --> 21:16.160
we'll use it when it's done.

21:16.200 --> 21:18.080
I'll shamelessly go and beg them.

21:18.110 --> 21:19.030
I'll use it too.

21:20.200 --> 21:20.730
Shengli,

21:24.900 --> 21:26.810
if you are shameless, I'll kiss your face.

21:26.810 --> 21:27.400
Come on.

21:27.400 --> 21:28.410
I'll drink to that.

21:28.410 --> 21:29.820
I'll drink to that.

21:33.480 --> 21:35.010
I'll kiss his face too.

21:35.400 --> 21:37.640
You've already finalized the poster,

21:37.770 --> 21:40.000
so how are you

21:40.390 --> 21:41.790
casting the female lead?

21:42.110 --> 21:42.460
Yes.

21:43.270 --> 21:43.810
Well,

21:43.980 --> 21:44.680
to be honest,

21:44.680 --> 21:46.650
I don't have the power

21:46.680 --> 21:47.810
to decide the female lead,

21:47.810 --> 21:49.340
but let me make a statement.

21:50.090 --> 21:53.220
If my next project works out,

21:53.550 --> 21:55.710
I'll cast Ranran as the female lead.

21:55.830 --> 21:56.240
Okay.

21:56.530 --> 21:57.840
Then Zhuang Zhuang

21:58.010 --> 21:59.640
can sing the theme song for us.

21:59.640 --> 22:00.590
Good.

22:00.880 --> 22:01.500
Alright.

22:01.530 --> 22:02.610
Then for this project,

22:02.610 --> 22:04.370
let me play a role first.

22:04.480 --> 22:06.010
But you don't kiss his face.

22:06.240 --> 22:07.140
Okay.

22:07.200 --> 22:08.000
No.

22:08.830 --> 22:09.290
No.

22:09.960 --> 22:11.220
Actually,

22:12.640 --> 22:15.510
there is a role.

22:15.530 --> 22:16.470
What role?

22:16.720 --> 22:18.290
It's a

22:18.330 --> 22:20.450
plumber.

22:21.270 --> 22:23.480
Stop joking. What are you saying?

22:24.070 --> 22:25.930
Unclogging drains.

22:27.900 --> 22:31.300
Repairing ACs, Unclogging drains.

22:31.330 --> 22:33.010
-Stop it.
-He basically plays himself.

22:33.010 --> 22:35.310
-Let's drink.
-I'll try.

22:35.880 --> 22:36.880
Okay.

22:36.940 --> 22:37.940
I've kissed your face.

22:37.940 --> 22:38.870
I'll try my best.

22:39.310 --> 22:41.660
Liquor is made from sorghum water.

22:41.770 --> 22:43.850
It's good stuff.

22:44.220 --> 22:45.480
Every day I...

22:46.700 --> 22:47.220
Guys,

22:47.480 --> 22:48.140
cut it out.

22:48.290 --> 22:50.140
The whole hallway is full of your voices.

22:50.140 --> 22:51.810
Who's going to pay the bill?

22:51.920 --> 22:52.980
Our front desk is getting off work soon.

22:52.980 --> 22:54.000
We're not saying we won't pay.

22:54.000 --> 22:55.480
We haven't finished eating
or drinking yet.

22:55.480 --> 22:56.940
We'll pay when we're done.

22:57.030 --> 22:57.560
Yeah.

22:57.590 --> 22:58.240
Our waiter

22:58.240 --> 22:59.110
has come in several times.

22:59.110 --> 22:59.570
You keep asking for this

22:59.570 --> 23:00.200
and that.

23:00.330 --> 23:01.160
No matter how many times you come in,

23:01.160 --> 23:03.420
-we have to eat before paying.
-No, no, bro.

23:03.420 --> 23:05.400
We'll pay when we're done.

23:05.430 --> 23:06.790
We will definitely pay.

23:06.980 --> 23:08.030
Don't worry about that.

23:08.030 --> 23:08.610
Wait, what do you mean?

23:08.610 --> 23:09.750
You trying to skip out on the bill?

23:09.750 --> 23:11.660
We never said that.

23:11.690 --> 23:13.690
Why do you have such an attitude?

23:13.810 --> 23:14.550
Watch your tone.

23:14.550 --> 23:15.290
So what?

23:16.250 --> 23:16.960
What do you mean, so what?

23:16.960 --> 23:17.620
How about

23:18.810 --> 23:19.590
changing places?

23:19.590 --> 23:20.480
Okay.

23:20.500 --> 23:21.310
Let's change places.

23:21.310 --> 23:22.460
Okay, let's change places.

23:22.460 --> 23:24.070
Give us a discount,
then we'll settle the bill.

23:24.070 --> 23:24.680
No discounts.

23:24.680 --> 23:25.940
The bill is right here.

23:31.640 --> 23:33.700
This steak isn't even cooked through

23:33.960 --> 23:35.360
and there is no discount,

23:37.200 --> 23:38.060
so we can't pay.

23:39.750 --> 23:41.480
I guess this is your first time.

23:42.380 --> 23:44.040
I figure you're not used to it.

23:44.460 --> 23:45.010
Here,

23:45.010 --> 23:45.850
our steaks are cooked

23:45.850 --> 23:48.010
medium-rare, medium, or medium-well.

23:48.010 --> 23:48.720
If not specified,

23:48.720 --> 23:50.110
we cook them medium.

23:50.700 --> 23:51.830
Are you going to eat it?

23:51.830 --> 23:52.700
Are you trying to argue with me?

23:52.700 --> 23:54.100
I want it well-done.

23:54.460 --> 23:55.570
Give me a well-done one.

23:55.570 --> 23:56.780
Heat it up right now.

23:56.900 --> 23:57.920
Take it and heat it up!

23:57.920 --> 23:59.520
All right, all right.

23:59.640 --> 24:00.740
I knew you'd pull this.

24:00.740 --> 24:01.360
Right?

24:01.510 --> 24:02.550
You get drunk and start causing trouble,

24:02.550 --> 24:03.010
right?

24:03.050 --> 24:03.980
Who's causing trouble?

24:03.980 --> 24:05.530
How many times have you rushed us?

24:05.530 --> 24:07.190
How many times did we rush you?

24:07.240 --> 24:07.980
Don't touch me!

24:07.980 --> 24:09.030
Look here.

24:09.240 --> 24:10.810
You look quite young.

24:11.110 --> 24:12.310
Why are you so unreasonable?

24:12.310 --> 24:13.200
You're older,

24:13.270 --> 24:14.660
but you're the most unreasonable one!

24:14.660 --> 24:16.720
Hey, watch your mouth!

24:16.900 --> 24:17.880
Don't touch me with your dirty hands!

24:17.880 --> 24:19.190
You're just a plumber!

24:22.400 --> 24:24.400
Who are you calling a plumber?

24:26.050 --> 24:27.010
Apologize.

24:27.350 --> 24:28.950
Apologize to us. Apologize.

24:35.500 --> 24:35.980
Look.

24:36.500 --> 24:37.230
Right there.

24:37.330 --> 24:39.310
The male and female leads in our movie

24:39.310 --> 24:41.370
broke up right under the watchtower.

24:41.530 --> 24:42.590
Director Weng said

24:42.740 --> 24:44.350
he'll shoot all the most beautiful spots

24:44.350 --> 24:45.150
in Beijing,

24:45.460 --> 24:46.240
But for here,

24:46.240 --> 24:47.810
he will save it to film in winter.

24:47.810 --> 24:49.550
In winter, it's even more beautiful here.

24:49.550 --> 24:51.290
Golden roofs and red walls,

24:51.400 --> 24:52.510
with heavy snow

24:52.660 --> 24:53.980
and the corners of life.

24:53.980 --> 24:55.220
One turns left,

24:55.250 --> 24:56.510
the other turns right.

24:56.980 --> 24:58.480
That sounds very moving.

24:59.510 --> 25:00.310
The two of them

25:00.350 --> 25:01.480
had a misunderstanding,

25:01.480 --> 25:02.530
so on their journey of life,

25:02.530 --> 25:04.060
they kept going in circles.

25:04.640 --> 25:05.460
I know.

25:05.900 --> 25:06.790
It's the part

25:06.900 --> 25:07.830
where there's always a misunderstanding

25:07.830 --> 25:09.310
that can't be explained clearly.

25:09.310 --> 25:10.250
How do you know?

25:12.940 --> 25:14.090
I dreamed about it.

25:14.240 --> 25:15.960
Right, you've read this script.

25:15.960 --> 25:18.020
You even helped me copy it many times.

25:18.510 --> 25:19.240
Come on, stand there.

25:19.240 --> 25:20.440
I'll take a picture of you.

25:20.440 --> 25:21.100
Stand here.

25:21.350 --> 25:21.720
Okay.

25:21.740 --> 25:22.490
Okay, come.

25:22.700 --> 25:23.310
Ready?

25:24.220 --> 25:26.090
1, 2, 3.

25:26.790 --> 25:27.490
One more.

25:28.180 --> 25:30.290
One, two, three.

25:30.770 --> 25:31.170
Great.

25:35.160 --> 25:37.240
What if we

25:37.640 --> 25:38.960
also went

25:39.010 --> 25:40.070
our separate ways?

25:41.500 --> 25:42.560
That won't happen.

25:43.000 --> 25:43.960
Wherever you go,

25:43.960 --> 25:44.990
I'll go too.

25:45.400 --> 25:47.400
We won't go in opposite directions.

25:48.000 --> 25:48.720
Did you tell your parents

25:48.720 --> 25:50.000
about your movie?

25:50.020 --> 25:50.620
Yes, I did.

25:50.640 --> 25:51.910
My mom is thrilled.

25:52.400 --> 25:54.110
Although my dad didn't say it,

25:54.160 --> 25:55.980
I think he's quite happy too.

25:57.420 --> 25:58.330
What about your family?

25:58.330 --> 25:59.190
How is your mom?

25:59.350 --> 26:00.410
She's doing great.

26:00.830 --> 26:02.630
I called her a couple of days ago,

26:02.660 --> 26:03.770
but she was at my aunt's house,

26:03.770 --> 26:05.030
so we didn't talk much.

26:06.220 --> 26:07.180
I was thinking of

26:07.220 --> 26:09.040
coming back for a visit

26:09.200 --> 26:10.180
and celebrating the good news

26:10.180 --> 26:11.320
with Mom.

26:11.810 --> 26:13.240
You have a competition coming up.

26:13.240 --> 26:14.900
Isn't it too tiring to go back?

26:15.070 --> 26:16.330
It's just for two days.

26:17.050 --> 26:18.090
My mom's always been the one

26:18.090 --> 26:19.110
quietly supporting my singing

26:19.110 --> 26:20.440
behind the scenes.

26:21.290 --> 26:23.720
And I came back in such a rush
for the holidays.

26:23.720 --> 26:24.720
I kind of miss her.

26:25.830 --> 26:26.400
How about

26:26.400 --> 26:27.510
I go back with you?

26:28.010 --> 26:29.660
Just focus on your own work.

26:30.350 --> 26:31.680
I'll be back in two days.

26:33.130 --> 26:34.720
Then I'll buy some
date pastries for your mom

26:34.720 --> 26:35.480
for you to take back.

26:35.480 --> 26:35.810
Okay.

26:35.900 --> 26:37.830
Let's go. I'll take you to buy some.

26:38.350 --> 26:39.980
I'm back!

26:41.550 --> 26:42.070
Mom!

26:43.790 --> 26:44.420
Mr. Ye.

26:49.570 --> 26:50.370
Where are you?

27:21.770 --> 27:22.630
Zhuang Zhuang.

27:30.080 --> 27:34.150
[No Smoking]

27:47.740 --> 27:49.750
Didn't I tell you to go home and rest?

27:50.350 --> 27:51.240
Why did you...

27:56.740 --> 27:58.540
Zhuang Zhuang, why are you here?

27:59.720 --> 28:02.200
Aren't you supposed to
be in a competition?

28:03.440 --> 28:05.240
Mom, how long have you been sick?

28:08.010 --> 28:09.640
I'm not sick.

28:10.290 --> 28:11.610
I am so delicate,

28:12.050 --> 28:13.650
I wouldn't mistreat myself.

28:14.440 --> 28:16.180
I just felt a little uncomfortable,

28:16.180 --> 28:17.660
so I came to the hospital.

28:17.680 --> 28:19.420
The doctor told me everything.

28:19.750 --> 28:21.210
I saw the medical report.

28:25.830 --> 28:27.920
Medical technology is so advanced

28:27.960 --> 28:28.820
these days.

28:28.900 --> 28:30.350
It's just a minor surgery.

28:30.350 --> 28:31.680
I'll be fine after that.

28:36.880 --> 28:37.440
Mom,

28:38.660 --> 28:39.610
since you are sick,

28:39.610 --> 28:41.410
let's get you treated properly.

28:41.680 --> 28:42.290
In this matter,

28:42.290 --> 28:44.000
you have to listen to me and cooperate.

28:44.000 --> 28:44.910
We are in this together.

28:44.910 --> 28:46.140
But your competition...

28:46.140 --> 28:46.880
It's in two months.

28:46.880 --> 28:48.080
Don't worry about it.

28:50.420 --> 28:51.460
If you really want me

28:51.460 --> 28:53.060
to focus on the competition,

28:53.510 --> 28:54.730
you should rest well

28:54.770 --> 28:56.400
and cooperate with the treatment

28:56.400 --> 28:57.330
to get well soon.

29:01.070 --> 29:03.180
Okay, I understand.

29:03.810 --> 29:04.740
On major issues,

29:04.770 --> 29:06.280
I know what to do.

29:06.640 --> 29:08.140
I won't put you in a tough spot

29:08.140 --> 29:10.170
and burden your mind.

29:10.830 --> 29:11.810
It's okay.

29:15.250 --> 29:17.250
It's fine. Everything will be fine.

29:17.770 --> 29:18.960
There, there. Don't cry.

29:18.960 --> 29:20.390
It's okay.

29:21.000 --> 29:22.240
It's fine.

29:22.400 --> 29:23.180
Stop crying.

29:41.580 --> 29:42.910
Zongbao, I told you—

29:42.940 --> 29:44.940
just leave me alone. I'm not eating.

30:02.240 --> 30:05.170
You've been making
all the meals these past few days?

30:10.030 --> 30:11.830
Zongbao said you're not eating.

30:14.310 --> 30:15.970
I just don't have an appetite.

30:17.850 --> 30:19.440
Don't make any more for me.

30:20.640 --> 30:22.830
I can adjust my condition myself.

30:23.880 --> 30:25.940
Why are you always worrying about me?

30:27.050 --> 30:29.250
You should be thinking about your work—

30:29.350 --> 30:30.420
how to act,

30:30.450 --> 30:32.310
how to make good films, big films.

30:34.900 --> 30:36.050
We will both be fine.

30:49.110 --> 30:51.040
Look, I'm gonna be honest with you—

30:51.050 --> 30:53.510
you're too simple.

30:53.920 --> 30:55.680
That's why you don't

30:55.700 --> 30:57.560
really understand making money.

30:59.380 --> 31:00.560
Starting from

31:00.610 --> 31:01.380
today,

31:02.610 --> 31:03.760
we are

31:04.740 --> 31:05.700
breaking up.

31:26.180 --> 31:26.770
Her eyebrows are

31:26.770 --> 31:28.090
still a bit asymmetrical.

31:28.090 --> 31:29.570
Please adjust them a bit more.

31:29.570 --> 31:29.960
Okay.

31:31.220 --> 31:32.680
Can it be a bit higher here?

31:34.160 --> 31:35.000
Sure.

31:35.090 --> 31:35.850
Use the hairdryer

31:35.730 --> 31:39.850
[Dressing Room]

31:35.870 --> 31:36.870
to blow it up a bit.

31:37.110 --> 31:38.440
Okay, I'll do it in a bit.

31:41.660 --> 31:42.520
Ranran is here.

31:42.670 --> 31:44.140
You guys go sit over there and do it.

31:44.140 --> 31:45.160
Ms. Ranran, here.

31:45.900 --> 31:46.770
Here.

31:50.590 --> 31:52.080
It's fine.

31:52.180 --> 31:53.050
Sit here.

31:53.050 --> 31:54.050
I'll do it for you.

31:56.350 --> 31:57.270
Ms. Ranran,

31:57.530 --> 31:58.740
that crying scene you just did

31:58.740 --> 31:59.880
was incredible.

32:00.050 --> 32:01.180
That one scene alone

32:01.200 --> 32:02.940
really brought the character to life.

32:02.940 --> 32:03.900
You're super impressive.

32:03.900 --> 32:04.440
Yeah,

32:04.680 --> 32:06.340
we were all moved watching it.

32:07.420 --> 32:08.020
Thank you.

32:08.250 --> 32:10.010
Ms. Ranran, you're still in makeup, right?

32:10.010 --> 32:10.570
Manager Zhang.

32:10.570 --> 32:11.000
Hello, Manager Zhang.

32:11.000 --> 32:11.600
Keep busy.

32:11.960 --> 32:13.050
I specifically came to see

32:13.050 --> 32:14.030
our Ms. Ranran.

32:14.220 --> 32:15.080
Manager Zhang.

32:15.810 --> 32:18.230
That scene just now was fantastic.

32:18.610 --> 32:19.870
I specifically got you

32:19.980 --> 32:21.640
some imported mineral water.

32:21.750 --> 32:22.400
I prepared

32:22.420 --> 32:23.590
a private lounge for you.

32:23.590 --> 32:24.800
The AC is already on.

32:24.850 --> 32:26.270
Once you're done with makeup,

32:26.270 --> 32:27.290
you can go back to the lounge

32:27.290 --> 32:28.070
and comfortably

32:28.070 --> 32:29.730
read your script and make art.

32:29.940 --> 32:30.670
Sounds good?

32:32.570 --> 32:33.390
Mr. Xie,

32:33.940 --> 32:35.940
do a good job on our Ranran's makeup.

32:36.050 --> 32:36.650
Of course.

32:36.900 --> 32:39.100
She looks like a born leading lady.

32:39.420 --> 32:39.880
Indeed.

32:40.290 --> 32:42.060
I'll let you get back to work.

32:42.330 --> 32:43.500
Let me know if you need anything.

32:43.500 --> 32:43.880
Okay?

32:43.900 --> 32:44.930
-Okay.
-Go ahead.

32:45.550 --> 32:49.110
[Dressing Room]

32:45.750 --> 32:46.480
Do a good job.

32:47.140 --> 32:47.810
Take care.

32:48.050 --> 32:48.550
Bye.

32:55.920 --> 32:57.520
Thank you for your hard work.

32:57.680 --> 32:58.940
Here, have some water.

32:59.960 --> 33:01.900
-Ms. Wang, have some water.
-Thank you.

33:01.900 --> 33:03.120
I'm really sorry.

33:03.180 --> 33:05.580
The director might be in a hurry

33:06.140 --> 33:07.830
with the costume and set change.

33:07.830 --> 33:08.480
Thank you.

33:08.880 --> 33:10.720
We couldn't afford

33:10.770 --> 33:12.570
such expensive water on our own.

33:12.590 --> 33:14.450
We don't get such good treatment.

33:23.770 --> 33:24.610
It's fine.

33:24.670 --> 33:26.800
Your acting just now was really great.

33:27.010 --> 33:28.610
Don't take it to heart, okay?

33:29.010 --> 33:30.410
Let's start your makeup.

33:39.620 --> 33:40.660
[Spring is not Far Away]

34:10.880 --> 34:11.610
Ranran,

34:12.630 --> 34:13.889
I told you to come over,

34:14.010 --> 34:15.060
but you didn't.

34:15.110 --> 34:16.770
Why are you hiding here alone?

34:18.460 --> 34:19.050
All the

34:19.150 --> 34:20.550
famous producers and directors

34:20.550 --> 34:21.590
are in that room.

34:21.710 --> 34:23.760
Let me tell you the good news.

34:24.550 --> 34:27.080
Everyone's asking about your availability.

34:27.760 --> 34:29.000
One thing's for sure:

34:31.090 --> 34:31.949
you've made it.

34:38.710 --> 34:39.440
Mr. Chu,

34:40.780 --> 34:41.920
they didn't shoot

34:42.260 --> 34:44.010
much of my part in that project.

34:46.820 --> 34:48.150
If it were someone else,

34:52.130 --> 34:53.840
what would I pay?

34:55.820 --> 34:56.710
What's wrong,

34:57.620 --> 34:58.290
Ranran?

34:59.800 --> 35:00.660
What happened?

35:00.960 --> 35:02.960
Why are you suddenly asking me this?

35:04.190 --> 35:05.130
All along,

35:05.340 --> 35:06.650
relying on my own ability to act

35:06.650 --> 35:08.030
has been my greatest dream

35:08.030 --> 35:09.450
and the happiest thing.

35:09.960 --> 35:10.340
Then,

35:10.690 --> 35:12.090
your dream has come true.

35:12.710 --> 35:14.420
You should be happy now.

35:16.610 --> 35:17.530
I am not happy.

35:35.280 --> 35:36.650
You can walk away from the role,

35:36.650 --> 35:38.510
but you will have to pay the price.

35:40.150 --> 35:41.280
You'll have to cover

35:41.510 --> 35:43.710
all the upfront costs:

35:45.050 --> 35:45.800
script development,

35:45.800 --> 35:47.130
costume, makeup, set design,

35:47.130 --> 35:47.990
camera, sound,

35:48.530 --> 35:49.980
art direction—

35:50.690 --> 35:51.940
every department.

35:55.630 --> 35:57.010
Let me put it this way.

35:57.480 --> 36:00.110
You're basically ruined in this industry.

36:04.980 --> 36:05.380
Stop.

36:06.320 --> 36:07.690
You've had enough.

36:08.130 --> 36:08.990
Stop drinking.

36:12.860 --> 36:13.540
Ranran,

36:14.230 --> 36:15.560
the first time I saw you,

36:16.780 --> 36:17.670
I fell for you.

36:21.780 --> 36:22.400
Look,

36:24.070 --> 36:25.420
so many actresses

36:26.980 --> 36:28.440
want to become stars.

36:29.280 --> 36:30.190
But how could they get

36:30.190 --> 36:32.120
such a good opportunity as you did?

36:32.840 --> 36:35.900
I used all my resources
to make you famous,

36:36.780 --> 36:38.180
but you don't cherish it.

36:39.280 --> 36:40.010
I don't want to see

36:40.010 --> 36:41.130
your future

36:42.840 --> 36:44.040
become so miserable.

36:45.550 --> 36:46.510
The reason I'm saying this

36:46.510 --> 36:47.250
is to tell you

36:47.300 --> 36:48.560
that I understand you.

36:49.400 --> 36:50.530
Everyone is rushing

36:50.550 --> 36:51.460
to get into this industry

36:51.460 --> 36:52.820
because it's glamorous.

36:52.820 --> 36:53.690
But you

36:55.610 --> 36:57.050
don't think it's that glamorous.

36:57.050 --> 36:57.870
Tell me, am I

36:58.900 --> 36:59.530
right?

37:01.070 --> 37:03.050
Of course, if you really don't
want to act anymore,

37:03.050 --> 37:04.210
I can help you.

37:15.670 --> 37:16.360
Mr. Chu,

37:17.320 --> 37:18.130
rest assured.

37:18.760 --> 37:20.170
I will definitely

37:20.170 --> 37:21.700
finish this show properly.

37:22.860 --> 37:23.380
Don't.

37:23.860 --> 37:24.260
Don't.

37:28.780 --> 37:29.260
Ranran,

37:34.710 --> 37:35.310
remember:

37:36.880 --> 37:38.540
don't push yourself too hard.

37:38.960 --> 37:39.860
I'm here.

37:40.360 --> 37:42.360
I won't let anyone hurt you.

37:44.860 --> 37:45.720
We'll walk away

37:46.650 --> 37:47.710
from this project.

37:48.920 --> 37:51.030
I'll handle all the compensation.

37:52.660 --> 37:54.460
You know I like you.

38:56.770 --> 38:58.740
I don't need anything you give me.

38:59.440 --> 39:00.980
Don't contact me again.

39:06.490 --> 39:10.860
[I Am a Stranger]

39:15.290 --> 39:15.830
[Golden Garden at Sunset]

39:18.390 --> 39:21.370
[Golden Garden at Sunset]

39:28.510 --> 39:29.280
You know,

39:29.610 --> 39:30.530
over all these years,

39:30.530 --> 39:32.270
I've spent so much

39:32.320 --> 39:34.320
just hiring acting coaches for you.

39:34.740 --> 39:36.000
You are a money-loser.

39:38.400 --> 39:39.100
Mom,

39:39.920 --> 39:42.220
did you borrow money from Mr. Chu?

39:41.660 --> 39:42.470
[Love Debt]

39:43.110 --> 39:46.440
[I Am a Stranger]

39:47.030 --> 39:48.230
Of everyone I've met,

39:49.010 --> 39:50.150
you set

39:51.570 --> 39:52.830
the highest standard.

39:52.960 --> 39:54.470
Big star Shen,

39:54.500 --> 39:56.380
your success is just around the corner.

39:56.380 --> 39:57.590
My dream of art

39:57.690 --> 40:00.410
will surely bloom beautifully

40:00.500 --> 40:02.010
and fragrantly.

40:03.810 --> 40:06.770
[Name: Shen Ranran] [Film Performance Art]

40:49.800 --> 40:50.660
Director Weng,

40:50.690 --> 40:51.610
I called Xu Shengli for you.

40:51.610 --> 40:52.740
He'll be right here.

40:53.070 --> 40:54.500
I've seen your plays.

40:54.650 --> 40:55.710
I really like them.

40:56.230 --> 40:57.440
I am Little Northeasterner.

40:57.440 --> 40:59.280
I'm the boss of Seasons Change Hostel.

40:59.280 --> 41:00.340
Come to our place when you have time.

41:00.340 --> 41:01.440
I'll treat you to a meal.

41:01.440 --> 41:02.900
Who needs you to treat him?

41:03.170 --> 41:04.030
Director Weng,

41:04.380 --> 41:04.980
has the start date for our play

41:04.980 --> 41:06.140
been decided yet?

41:06.630 --> 41:07.320
Xu,

41:09.980 --> 41:12.230
Oh no. I'm done.

41:13.210 --> 41:14.520
Mr. Sui

41:14.940 --> 41:16.500
ran away with money.

41:20.460 --> 41:24.010
["The Late Love"
Filming Team–Producer's Office]

41:22.340 --> 41:22.900
Xu,

41:23.650 --> 41:25.280
how is it? Did you find him?

41:25.940 --> 41:27.130
His family went abroad

41:27.130 --> 41:28.200
a few months ago.

41:28.690 --> 41:29.820
The police also said

41:29.900 --> 41:30.920
he used our project

41:30.920 --> 41:32.180
to scam many investors

41:32.210 --> 41:33.340
out of a lot of money.

41:33.410 --> 41:37.470
[The Late Love Filming Team]

41:35.280 --> 41:36.090
So, Director,

41:36.320 --> 41:37.360
are we really not

41:37.530 --> 41:39.060
making this movie anymore?

41:39.860 --> 41:40.920
Xu,

41:42.170 --> 41:43.300
when making a movie,

41:44.400 --> 41:45.820
anything can happen.

41:46.530 --> 41:47.010
Wait,

41:47.830 --> 41:48.860
we've gone through

41:48.860 --> 41:50.100
so much trouble.

41:50.210 --> 41:51.210
We bet

41:51.210 --> 41:52.210
our lives on this.

41:52.320 --> 41:53.860
Aren't we sincere enough?

41:54.960 --> 41:55.490
Shengli,

42:00.500 --> 42:02.060
no matter how well you plan,

42:02.760 --> 42:04.490
you can't predict everything.

42:05.510 --> 42:06.110
By the way,

42:06.550 --> 42:07.160
you

42:07.420 --> 42:08.210
better go to the bank

42:08.210 --> 42:09.630
and check how

42:09.630 --> 42:10.460
your loan contract was signed.

42:10.460 --> 42:11.360
Why should I care about

42:11.360 --> 42:12.510
my contract?

42:12.720 --> 42:14.320
What about our crew?

42:17.110 --> 42:19.900
Well, the studio's money

42:20.230 --> 42:21.210
was supposed to be given

42:21.210 --> 42:23.070
when you were halfway through.

42:23.090 --> 42:23.920
So at least

42:24.000 --> 42:25.330
we don't owe the studio.

42:25.650 --> 42:28.170
We borrowed 500,000 yuan from the bank.

42:29.400 --> 42:30.760
Before shooting,

42:31.880 --> 42:33.570
we spent

42:33.570 --> 42:34.720
about 100,000 yuan,

42:34.920 --> 42:35.760
which came from

42:35.760 --> 42:36.940
our loan.

42:37.280 --> 42:38.010
The rest

42:38.530 --> 42:39.420
was taken away

42:39.420 --> 42:40.170
by Mr. Sui.

42:40.170 --> 42:41.130
Then there's the

42:41.130 --> 42:42.390
actors' upfront fees,

42:43.260 --> 42:45.890
set construction, and staff salaries—

42:46.010 --> 42:47.570
we'll have the Manager tally that up.

42:47.570 --> 42:48.480
Like I said,

42:49.280 --> 42:50.860
every play has its own fate.

42:51.560 --> 42:56.230
[The Late Love Filming Team]

42:52.300 --> 42:54.330
No matter how unacceptable it is,

42:55.010 --> 42:55.980
you have to accept it.
